reviewText: Finally! According to TVShowsOnDVD Shout Factory has licensed Leave It To Beaver from Universal and will release a season 3 set on June 15, 2010 and a Complete Series set on June 29, 2010.  The fourth season is set to be released on September 14, 2010, with the final 2 seasons to follow in individual sets thereafter. They are remastering all episodes and are producing bonus material too! This is the best news possible for this series, Shout Factory always does a great job on the shows they rescue.

reviewText: This is actually the last season that Beaver was a little boy. Seasons 5 and 6, he was becoming a young man. reviewText: Okay, folks, there is ONE reason you must buy this season's set...it's called "In The Soup."  That's right, this is the season where the Beaver falls into the cup of "soup" on the billboard, and needs to be rescued. If that doesn't convince you, there are so many other good episodes that I don't know how anyone could not enjoy it. They've included a nice bonus on this set:  An interview with Tony Dow. Serious fans, you must have this set for your collection.

Title: Leave it to Beaver - Season 4

reviewText: The fourth season of Leave It To Beaver aired from 1960 to 1961. This set has all 39 uncut and remastered episodes spread out over 6 single-sided dual-layered dvds.The episodes on this set are:Disc One:01. Beaver Won't Eat02. Beaver's House Guest03. Beaver Becomes a Hero04. Wally, the Lifeguard05. Beaver's Freckles06. Beaver's Big Contest07. Miss Lander's FianceDisc Two:08. Eddie's Double-Cross09. Beaver's I.Q.10. Wally's Glamour Girl11. Chuckie's New Shoes12. Beaver and Kenneth13. Beaver's AccordianDisc Three:14. Uncle Billy15. Teacher's Daughter16. Ward's Millions17. Beaver's Secret Life18. Wally's Track Meet19. Beaver's Old Buddy20. Beaver's TonsilsDisc Four:21. The Big Fish Count22. Beaver's Poster23. Mother's Helper24. The Dramatic Club25. Wally and Dudley26. Eddie Spends the NightDisc Five:27. Beaver's Report Card28. Mistaken Identity29. Wally's Dream Girl30. The School Picture31. Beaver's Rat32. In the Soup33. Community ChestDisc Six:34. Junior Fire Chief35. Beaver's Frogs36. Beaver Goes in Business37. Kite Day38. Beaver's Doll Buggy39. Substitute FatherVideo: Shout Factory went all-out and did an incredible job remastering Leave It To Beaver. The show is presented in its original full frame 1:33 ratio and looks fantastic. The show is in black & white and looks clean, sharp, and bright.Audio: The only audio track on this set is English 2.0 mono. It is clear sounding and I have no complaintsSubtitles: There are no subtitles on the set but it is close-captioned in English only.
summary: I'm not just giving you the business Sam, this is one swell dvd set
